{
  "buggy_files": ["drivers/acpi/video_detect.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["video_detect_dmi_table"],
  "confidence": 0.85,
  "reasoning": "The Acer TravelMate 5735Z is missing from the DMI quirks table in video_detect.c. The system lacks proper ACPI video backlight capability detection (_DOD/_DOS methods), causing it to default to vendor backlight which doesn't work with function keys. When the user explicitly boots with acpi_backlight=native, the backlight works correctly. The fix is to add a DMI entry to the video_detect_dmi_table to force native backlight for this system. The buggy_functions refers to the data structure (video_detect_dmi_table) that needs to be extended with a new entry for this Acer model matching DMI_SYS_VENDOR 'Acer' and DMI_PRODUCT_NAME 'TravelMate 5735Z' with callback video_detect_force_native."
}

